The '''ABU Radio Song Festival 2015''' was the third edition of the [[ABU Radio Song Festival]]s, organised by the [[Asia-Pacific Broadcasting Union]] (ABU). Originally a [[wikt:biennial|biennial]] event, the festival organisers changed its format to an annual festival commencing from [[ABU Radio Song Festival 2014|2014]]. The festival took place on 29 May 2015 in the city of [[Yangon]], [[Myanmar]]. Seventeen songs had been submitted to the event organisers, of which only ten songs from nine countries, were selected to perform at the event. The hosts {{Abucnty|Myanmar|r=Radio}} made their début in the festival.
==Location== {{details|topic=the host city|Yangon}} It was announced that the 2015 ABU Radio Song Festival will take place in [[Yangon]], [[Myanmar]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.abu.org.my/Festivals-@-ABU_Radio_Song_Festival.aspx |title=ABU Radio Song Festival 2015 |publisher=ABU |accessdate=9 November 2014 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141204211032/http://www.abu.org.my/Festivals-%40-ABU_Radio_Song_Festival.aspx |archivedate=4 December 2014 |df=dmy }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=ARSF’15: Venue For ABU Radio Song Festival Announced|url=http://eurovoix.com/2015/05/07/arsf15-venue-for-abu-radio-song-festival-announced/ |website=Eurovoix|accessdate=7 May 2015|date=7 May 2015}}</ref>
== Format == Unlike the format used in the [[Eurovision Song Contest]] there are two versions of the Song Festivals, [[ABU Radio Song Festival|ABU Radio]] and [[ABU TV Song Festival|ABU TV]] Song Festivals. The ABU Radio Song Festival which will take place on 29 May 2015 coincides with the Radio Asia 2015 event that took place between 28–30 May 2015.<ref name="RA15">{{cite web|title=Radio Asia 2015|url=http://www.abu.org.my/Event-_-RAC2015.aspx|publisher=ABU|accessdate=15 March 2015}}</ref>
===Host broadcaster=== [[Myanmar Radio and Television]] (MRTV), will be the host broadcaster for the festival on 29 May 2015.<ref name="Radio2015">{{cite web|last1=Granger|first1=Anthony|title=Myanmar to host ABU Radio Song Festival 2015|url=http://eurovoix.com/2014/11/09/myanmar-to-host-abu-radio-song-festival-2015/|website=eurovoix.com|publisher=Eurovoix|accessdate=9 November 2014|date=9 November 2014}}</ref>
===Interval act=== The interval acted featured Rosanita Niken, Billy Talahatu and Stella, performing the song "Pusaka".<ref>{{cite web|last1=Granger|first1=Anthony|title=ARSF’15: Interval Act Song Released|url=http://eurovoix.com/2015/05/10/arsf15-interval-act-song-released/|website=eurovoix.com|publisher=Eurovoix|accessdate=10 May 2015|date=10 May 2015}}</ref>
==Participating countries== {{Details|ABU Radio Song Festival#Participation}} A total of seventeen countries took part in this years festival.<ref name="Confirmed Participants">{{cite web|last1=Granger|first1=Anthony|title=ARSF’15: 14 Songs Selected For The ABU Radio Song Festival|url=http://eurovoix.com/2015/04/23/arsf15-14-songs-selected-for-the-abu-radio-song-festival/|website=Eurovoix.com|accessdate=23 April 2015}}</ref> Host country Myanmar made their début in this years festival along with the Maldives and Palestine. Vietnam and Indonesia also returned to the contest after not participating in 2014. However Australia and Iran both withdrew from the contest.
