{{Infobox book | name = Spilt Milk | title_orig = Leite Derramado | translator = [[Alison Entrekin]] | image = | caption = | author = [[Chico Buarque]] | illustrator = | cover_artist = | country = [[Brazil]] | language = [[Portuguese language|Portuguese]] | series = | subject = | genre = | publisher = Companhia das Letras | release_date = 2009 | english_release_date = 2012 | media_type = | pages = 195 | oclc = | preceded_by = | followed_by = }}
'''''Spilt Milk''''' (original title in [[Portuguese language|Portuguese]]: ''Leite Derramado'') is a novel written by [[Chico Buarque]].
== Synopsis == A very old man is in a hospital bed. A member of a traditional Brazilian family, he presents the history of his family in a monologue addressed to his daughter, the nurses, and anyone else who will listen. He follows his family's path from his Portuguese ancestors, including a baron of the [[Empire of Brazil|Empire]], and a [[First Brazilian Republic|First Republic's]] Senator, down to his grandson, a youth from [[Rio de Janeiro]]. His family saga is characterized by social and economic decadence against the background of Brazilian history over the last two centuries.
==Awards and Recognitions== *Voted best book of 2009 by readers of ''[[O Globo]]''.<ref>{{cite news |title='Leite derramado', de Chico Buarque, é o melhor livro de 2009 para leitores do site |url=http://oglobo.globo.com/cultura/mat/2009/12/27/leite-derramado-de-chico-buarque-o-melhor-livro-de-2009-para-leitores-do-site-915371813.asp |work=[[O Globo]] |date=28 December 2009 |accessdate=6 January 2010 }}</ref> *[[São Paulo Prize for Literature#2010 São Paulo Prize for Literature|2010 São Paulo Prize for Literature]] — Shortlisted in the Best Book of the Year category<ref name=folha2010>{{cite web |url=http://www1.folha.uol.com.br/ilustrada/742784-premio-sao-paulo-de-literatura-divulga-finalistas.shtml |title=Prêmio São Paulo de Literatura divulga finalistas |work=[[Folha de S.Paulo]] |author=[[MARCO RODRIGO ALMEIDA]] |date=29 May 2010 |accessdate=6 April 2013}}</ref>
==Editions== '''Brazilian edition''' *''Leite Derramado'', São Paulo, SP: Companhia das Letras, 2009. {{ISBN|978-8-5359-1411-5}} '''Translations''' *[[English language|English]] translation by [[Alison Entrekin]], ''Spilt Milk'', New York, NY: Grove Press, 2012. {{ISBN|978-0-8021-2008-3}} *[[French language|French]] translation by [[Geneviève Leibrich]], ''Quand je sortirai d'ici'', Paris: Gallimard, 2011. {{ISBN|978-2-07-012817-4}} *[[German language|German]] translation by [[Karin von Schweder-Schreiner]], ''Vergossene Milch'', Frankfurt am Main: S. Fischer, 2013. {{ISBN|978-3-10-046331-9}} *[[Italian language|Italian]] translation by [[Roberto Francavilla]], ''Latte versato'', Milano: Feltrinelli, 2010. {{ISBN|978-8-80-701803-9}} *[[Spanish language|Spanish]] translation by [[Ana Rita da Costa García]], ''Leche derramada'', Barcelona: Salamandra, 2010. {{ISBN|978-8-49-838340-9}}
